President Donald Trump issued a proclamation on January 15, 2021, recognizing Religious Freedom Day. In the proclamation, he emphasized the importance of faith and religious freedom in the history and character of the United States. He stated that his administration has worked to protect and promote religious liberty, including through executive orders and policies that defend the rights of religious individuals, communities, and organizations. He also highlighted efforts to support religious healthcare providers and educational institutions. The proclamation acknowledged the global issue of religious persecution and affirmed the United States' commitment to expanding religious liberty worldwide. President Trump called on all Americans to commemorate Religious Freedom Day and to work towards safeguarding and preserving religious freedom both domestically and internationally.